From 7ba366a11dbe1f472ada0b84625efd56091938be Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 22:36:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(hooks): resolve t3-review note indirection + tier its
 destination
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The colleague-review note path `t3 review post-comment <repo> <mr> <note>`
carries its body as the positional NOTE and posts to a GitLab project path.
Two over-blocks of legitimate colleague-review posts are closed.

#1780 — the positional NOTE's `$(cat <path>)` / `$VAR` indirection now resolves
to its real content exactly like a `--body` flag value. `resolve_inline_body_value`
gains an in-command heredoc / printf-redirect body fallback (the referenced file
is not on disk at PreToolUse), threaded through `append_t3_review_note_payload`.
A `t3` publish segment is also recognised as a parseable leader so a `$(cat …)`
note body is no longer misread as an opaque hidden forge transport; an
unresolvable indirection still fails closed.

#1937 — the NOTE's positional `<repo>` is now resolved as a destination and
classified PUBLIC vs INTERNAL the same way a `gh`/`glab` `--repo` target is, so
an overlay-infra brand word native to a private internal namespace stops
false-positiving on an internal remote while the same word toward a public
surface still blocks.

The generic `[teatree]` list reader moves to `_repo_visibility` so the over-cap
`publish_destination` keeps shrinking.

Closes #1780
Closes #1937
